<p><i><span class="hilitdffcc99"><b>Euphanerops</b></span></a></i><b>:</b>&nbsp;<i>E. longaevus</i></p>
<p><b>Synonyms </b> <a name="Endeiolepis"></a><i>Endeiolepis aneri</i>, <i>Legendrelepis parenti</i></p>
<div class="taxrng"><p><a href="../../paleozoic/devonian/latedev.html">Late Devonian</a>.</p></div>
<div class="taxphl"><p> two to choose from:<br />
Janvier: <a href="#Hyperoartia">Hyperoartia</a> <b>:</b> <a href="#Petromyzontiformes">Petromyzontiformes</a> + *.<br />
<i>or</i> Sansom et al 2010: <a href="#Jamoytiiformes">Jamoytiiformes</a>: <a href="#Jamoytius"><i>Jamoytius</i></a> + *. </p></div>
<p><b>Characters:</b> tail strongly heterocercal; no mineralized exoskeleton ATW040314</p>
<p><b>Comment:</b> Probably cogeneric with <i>Euphanerops</i> MAK111022</p>
